	   <a name=98981246373482></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98981246373482><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3910&mid=98981246373482>Price for MotQ</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3910&mid=98981246373482#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 13th 11:54 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I bought an MotQ recently for 200pp at lvl 14. From the postings here and the recommended average it's difficult to tell whether I got a good price or not. The postings suggest the range is from 400 - 600pp but out in the real world most people sell it for between 250 - 350pp. I'm just wondering because, being only lvl 14, it comprised my entire life savings and I want to check I got a decent price for it since I had to forego upgrading some of my armour to bronze. In any case, I'm quite happy with it given that I'll have the time to practise 2hp. Used to have a Finely Crafted Shan'Tok with maxed out skill in 1hs that hit regularly for 18hps; MotQ misses and does 1hps damage frequently but as my skill increases it occasionally does 29hps damage. In a group that doesn't mind you practising it's ace, and you can always use your spells and tank-ability to supplement. In any case, I know I'll really appreciate it at later lvls. <br><br>PS Since this is my first and only character, I took the advice of higher lvl Pallies about keeping skills on an even keel till you can specialise at higher lvls and I'm keeping the Shan'Tok and a Sarnak Ceremonial Sword to practise 1hs and 2hs. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
