<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=98844554148507></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98844554148507><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3910&mid=98844554148507>Weapon Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3910&mid=98844554148507#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 28th 4:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Id like to throw in my 2cp. Im not sure what weapon skills are based on, but Im pretty sure it is Int. My room mate, who plays an SK, got a MoSS at level 45. His skill in 1hb was 5 at the time. All he did was fight the bards in Innothule and Feerrott and he had his skill up to about 60-70 in no time. My advice is find a critter on the same level as the bards (if you don't want the bard faction hit) and just keep killing them. Yes it was boring for him, but it only took about 8 RL hours to get his skill up to do decent damage to a MOB. BTW he also kept a reserve weapon that he was proficient in to do damage while in a group.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
